  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 88074e2e0d4f0b8478a99308a4b0d6a4, type: 3}
  m_Name: ScentedSprayMist
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: GameScripts::BlueMCQCard
  cardName: The Scented Spray Mist
  image: {fileID: 21300000, guid: 65c69c1a0e3d7ab4a98ac61e425b98a0, type: 3}
  statement: 
  question: Many sprays, paints, and cleaners release invisible gases called Volatile
    Organic Compounds (VOCs). These gases can hurt us and the Earth. What should
    we do when using one of these sprays at home?
  answers:
  - answer: Make sure the doors and windows are closed so none of the VOCs escape.
    messageWhenChosen: 'Oops! Your health and safety come first! Always open windows
      and doors when painting or spraying something with a strong smell.  '
    correctAnswer: 0
  - answer: "Open a window so that you don\u2019t breathe in any unhealthy chemicals. "
    messageWhenChosen: Correct! Your health and safety come first! Always open windows
      and doors when painting or spraying something with a strong smell.
    correctAnswer: 1
